<br>
Rather than chain summon, I keep summoning Decoys until I get one that hits for 46.  Then I outfit it with every AC item I can conjure.<br>
<br>
I pull a golem or snake with malosini and med a bit while the mob starts melting on the DS.  Then a Sirocco, maybe a pet heal, then another Sirocco if the first one was resisted, otherwise a Scar or two to finish off the mob.  Snakes require more nukes, the golems often only need one Sirocco.  <br>
<br>
The Decoy's lower level and weaker attack, coupled with it's strong damage shield makes it difficult for the pet to do more than 50% of the damage.  I've tried the same tactic with the 57 earth and definitely earn less exp.  Judging from the percent healed by the heal spell, the Decoy has maybe 85-90% of the hp of a 57 earth.<br>
<br>
I get about half a blue an hour.  Maybe chain summoning is more exp/mana efficient, but I tend to die more when chain summoning.<br>
<br>
It can be dangerous making your way to the Temple, always the chance something will see thru invis and then you've got a train on your hands.  Aside from that, I've found soloing near the temple safer than soloing along the zone wall and/or near the zone exits. <p>Shazar Oom <BR>
58 Conjurer <BR>
