<br>
Summon Water Pet for backstab.  Turn taunt off.<br>
<br>
Go down, boot a mob for 600, partner snares and roots, repeat process til mob is slightly less then half and not rooted anymore.  Send pet on mob and run off in different direction for another pull.  The pet backstabs the sh*t out of the mob and kills it really quick while Im off getting the next pull. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uylaine76.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ylaine76</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 328<br> <font color=#333333>(1/29/02 10:40:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=93.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: would like a mage partner here</span><hr size=1> Hm I found the shimmering rock fiends pretty easy to nuke with Shock of Steel<br>
